            "preprocessing": "5/7 - Implements configurable downsampling and Gaussian blur. Background subtraction exists but is optional and not integrated as an estimated background model (e.g., blur/morphological) when background is None, so the pipeline is good but not complete/robust for varying illumination.",
            "coarse_detection": "6/7 - Finds contours on thresholded downsampled image, selects largest contour, computes min enclosing circle, and scales center/radius back to original coordinates. Uses Otsu with fallback threshold; reasonable robustness though contour retrieval mode (RETR_TREE) and lack of morphological cleanup can hurt.",
            "fine_detection": "4/7 - Performs radial scanning over many angles and uses 1D intensity differences as a gradient proxy, but selects only the maximum absolute gradient (no explicit dual-edge rising/falling logic to pick inner edge vs outer edge), and sub-pixel refinement is only noted as a comment (not implemented).",
            "statistical_analysis": "5/7 - Computes MAD and applies a robust 3-sigma-like filter (MAD*1.4826). Outlier rejection is applied to radii before circle fitting, but the final radius is obtained from least-squares circle fit (not a robust estimator like median radius), and no fallback handling for MAD=0 is included.",
            "mask_generation": "3/7 - Creates a correct circular mask and supports a simple chord_cutoff-based cropping, but there is no actual chord detection logic, no adaptive horizontal cropping based on detected chords, and feature detection only includes a simplistic chord midpoint from a provided cutoff plus high-intensity sampling; outliers are just passed through from fine detection."
